06/12/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Outgoing Prime Minister Adrian Nastase predicted on Saturday (4 December) that the government would manage to complete accession negotiations with the EU before the Union summit on 17 December. 
Nastase said he is optimistic about closing the remaining two chapters, although he conceded that the talks on one chapter -- Competition -- were "very difficult".
In other news, Denmark announced on Saturday that it plans to extend about 700,000 euros to support Romania's preparations for EU membership. 
The money would be used for projects in the public administration and the NGO sectors. 
(Mediafax, Rompres - 06/12/04; Rompres - 04/12/04)
